<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="123" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="18.[136,1452,158,617]" pageId="18" pageNumber="123">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,729,230,256]" pageId="18" pageNumber="123">Distribution, habitat and conservation status:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="R. E. Fries" authorityYear="1908" box="[757,906,230,256]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="18" pageNumber="123" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="regnellii">
<emphasis box="[757,906,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="123">Sida regnellii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in 
<collectingCountry box="[1017,1131,230,256]" name="Argentina" pageId="18" pageNumber="123">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1141,1245,231,257]" name="Paraguay" pageId="18" pageNumber="123">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1298,1366,230,256]" name="Brazil" pageId="18" pageNumber="123">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="18" pageNumber="123">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[225,301,266,292]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="18" pageNumber="123">Paraná</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[358,572,266,292]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="18" pageNumber="123">Rio Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
states) (
<bibRefCitation author="Zuloaga, F. O. &amp; Morrone, O. &amp; Belgrano M. J." box="[668,895,266,292]" pageId="18" pageNumber="123" pagination="1 - 3348" refId="ref20813" refString="Zuloaga, F. O., Morrone, O. &amp; Belgrano M. J. (2008) Catalogo de las plantas vasculares del Cono Sur (Argentina, sur de Brasil, Chile, Paraguay y Uruguay). Monographs in Systematic Botany from the Missouri Botanical Garden 107: 1 - 3348." type="journal article" year="2008">
Zuloaga 
<emphasis box="[770,828,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="123">et al.</emphasis>
2008
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bovini, M. G." box="[908,1054,266,292]" pageId="18" pageNumber="123" refId="ref18092" refString="Bovini, M. G. (2020) Sida in Lista de Especies da Flora do Brasil. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. Available from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / jabot / floradobrasil / FB 9206 (accessed 7 July 2020)" type="url" year="2020">Bovini 2020</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingRegion box="[1105,1319,266,292]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="18" pageNumber="123">Rio Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
the species occurs in Inland sub-montane grassland, Bush grassland, Coastal grassland, 
<taxonomicName box="[1008,1098,302,328]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Aristida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="18" pageNumber="114" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Aristida</taxonomicName>
grassland, and in Shallow soil grassland (
<figureCitation box="[258,357,338,364]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="17.[136,229,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[267,1344,252,1880]" captionTargetId="figure-17@17.[205,1383,190,1929]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 8. Distribution map of Sida riedelii, S. ramoniana, S. regnellii, S. reitzii and S. tuberculata in Rio Grande do Sul state, Brazil." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415505/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="123">Figure 8</figureCitation>
). With the available records, the species is here considered Least Concern (LC) with an EOO of 
